2016-10-18  Sylvain Doremus  <dragonjoker59@hotmail.com>
	* Point light shadow maps are now a cube map array.
	* Fixed frame saving colours swap.
	* Fixed the lights problems I had when I applied a bias to the reference depth in shadow mapping.
	* It has allowed me to remove the fixed pipeline polygon offset that was applied instead of the bias in GLSL.
	* Modified GlslWriter::GetLocale to make it more type safe (removed the implementation with Expr, and the assignment parameter must now be of the template return type).
	* Removed LOCALE and LOCALE_ASSIGN macros, in GlslWriter.

2016-10-17  Sylvain Doremus  <dragonjoker59@hotmail.com>
	* Something really wrong I think...
	* Can't use samplerCubeArray for point lights (needs OpenGL 4.0, and layered rendering), so I'll keep the samplerCube for now.
	* I have a ShadowMapPassPoint that doesn't work, but that doesn't produce any OpenGL error anymore.
	* Spot light shadow mapping uses a sampler2DArrayShadow.
	* Context can now render one layer of a texture array (depth or not).

2016-10-16  Sylvain Doremus  <dragonjoker59@hotmail.com>
	* Modified textures storage management: the storage is now in the layout, and allocates on GPU all necessary memory to hold the data.
	* It has allowed me to use ImmutableStorage for cube maps too.
	* ShadowMapPass is now a base class, each light type implements its class.

2016-10-14  Sylvain Doremus  <dragonjoker59@hotmail.com>
	* Fixed non SSE2 support.
	* Spot lights shadow mapping is implemented.
	* Implemented diverse shadow types, and it can be specified through GLSL::LightingModel construction.
	* The shadow acne is handled through glPolygonOffset.
	* Fixed a bug in GLSL::Float.
	* Shadow mapping works, now I need to resolve the shadow acne.
	* Added shadow samplers, so soften the shadow edges.

