2015-10-27  Sylvain Doremus  <dragonjoker59@hotmail.com>
	* Render to texture works, still some work to do in RenderToBuffer to make it work (I use BlitInto, but it is not a viable solution). The problem came from DepthStencilState, with depth test enabled while I don't have Z component for Context::BToBRender.
	* Removed threaded plugins loading.
	* Removed FrameBuffer::RenderToBuffer method.
	* Renamed Context::BToBContext to Context::RenderTextureToCurrentBuffer.
	* Added Context::RenderTextureToBackBuffer, to handle Y inversion with Direct3D.
	* RenderTarget is no more resizable.
	* Fixed an alpha problem in Context::RenderTextureToCurrentBuffer.
	* Temporary fix for MsaaRenderTechnique, for DepthStencil buffers. I'll need to fix that properly using the method described here: http://www.gamedev.net/topic/602811-resolving-a-depthstencil-buffer/
	* Now RTOT works with D3D11.

